net.enilink.komma.model

Interface IModel.Factory

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    SerializableModelFactory
    Enclosing interface:
    IModel

    public static interface IModel.Factory
    A factory for creating resources.

    A factory is implemented to create a specialized type of resource and is typically registered in registry.

    See Also:
    IModelSet.createModel(URI)

    • Method Detail

      • createModel

        IModel createModel(IModelSet modelSet,
                   URI uri)
        Creates an model with the given URI and returns it.

        Clients will typically not call this directly themselves; it's called by the model set to create a model.

        Parameters:
        modelSet - the containing model set.
        uri - the URI.
        Returns:
        a new model.
        See Also:
        IModelSet.createModel(URI)
